Port Captain - PT Altus Lines Indonesia
Port Captain  -
Port Captain
Responsibilities
Plan deployment of floating crane to meet shipment schedule received from clients/shippers, in consultation with Jakarta and Singapore offices.Liaise with Master of the Floating Crane and Master of the Ocean-going vessel for pre-loading meeting, cargo operations planning, including loading sequence.Handle all agency matters for the floating crane, including appointment of agents in case of redeployment of the FC.Deal with port authorities, SEACOM, ADPEL, Syahbandar, as may be required.Monitor the rotation of coal barges from shipper and ensure maximum efficiency of FC for transhipment of coal cargo to OGV. Report any problems with transhipment including technical breakdowns which are affecting FC performance.To assist FC Master in supervision of cargo stowage, loading, trimming.Attend draft survey upon completion of loading for calculating final loaded quantity and at any other intermediate stages, as may be required.Provide assistance to FC Master in case of any incident/ accident involving damages to FC or OGV hul or equipment during loading operations. Liaise with local agents, port authorities and surveyors as necessary for arranging inspection of the damages and reporting same to office.Monitoring safety of FC during rough weather and guiding FC Master for shifting to safe anchorage as necessary.Preparation and checking of cargo related documentation along with Master of FC. Upon completion of shipment, Port Captain shall collect all cargo-related documentation such as B/L, SOF/ Time Sheet, Loading Report and send scanned copies of these to office.Maintaining close contact with FC Master and crew, and coordinationg with technical team to ensure optimum performance of the FCLiaising with clients/ shippers as local representative of company for commercial/ operational matters.  Candidate must possess at least a Bachelor's Degree, Logistic/Transportation, Maritime Studies or equivalent.Required skill(s): ANT III.Required language(s): English, Bahasa IndonesiaAt least 3 year(s) of working experience in the related field is required for this position.Preferably Supervisor / Coordinators specializing in Logistics/Supply Chain or equivalent.Full-Time position(s) available.
